  "title": "Associate a key with each map element",
  "body": "I'm trying to do this:\n\n``` jsx\nimport React from 'react'\nimport {RefinementList} from 'react-instantsearch'\n\nfunction CustomRefinementList (props) {\n  return (\n    {props.items.length &&\n      <section className='pa3 pa4-ns'>\n        <div className='f6 fw6 ttu tracked pb2 bb b--black-10 black-70'>{props.title}</div>\n        <RefinementList {...props} />\n      </section>\n    }\n  )\n}\n\nexport default RefinementList.connect(CustomRefinementLis\n```\n\nIt doesn't work because it's in a infinite rendering loop.\n\nBecause `RefinementList` and `List` element are generated dynamically, I think that the problem is because is necessary associate a `key` (related: https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/multiple-components.html#dynamic-children)\n",
